Package: tyler
Title: Common Functions for Mystery Caller or Audit Studies Evaluating Patient Access to Care
Version: 1.2.0
Authors@R: 
    person("Tyler", "Muffly", email = "tyler.muffly@dhha.org", role = c("aut", "cre"),
           comment = "ORCID: 0000-0002-2044-1693")
Description: The 'tyler' package provides tools to support mystery caller studies
    assessing patient access to care. Core functions retrieve and clean National
    Provider Identifier information, geocode addresses, build isochrone maps, and
    summarize provider demographics. Utility wrappers fetch US Census data,
    assemble tables, and generate exploratory plots. Example datasets like
    residency program listings and taxonomy codes showcase package workflows.
    Additional sample data includes physician location records.
    Functions like `split_and_save` help organize caller assignments, while `validate_and_remove_invalid_npi` cleans data prior to CMS lookups.
    HERE API integration enables batch drive-time isochrone creation, and vignettes walk through census data retrieval and NPI workflows in detail.
